\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f7\lang2057\f9\fs24\f7\lang1025\qj\tx540 2.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s1\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af7\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs24\lang2057\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 On 13 October 2000 Nationwide lodged a complaint with the Competition Commission against SAA.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0 Under the old rules of the Commission a complaint had to be accepted by the Commission before it constituted a complaint \'96 it appears that this complaint was accepted on the 17 October 2000. Note that in the complaint referral the Commission dates the fil
ing of the complaint on 18 October 2000.( See paragraph 5.1 of the complaint referral, Record page 4).}}}
{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af14\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af14\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 }  In brief the complaint alleged that SAA was trying to exclude it from the domestic airline market by engaging in a number of practices that were prohibited unde
r the Competition Act (the \'91Act\'92).  Four anti-competitive practices were alleged  \'96 (i) SAA was engaged in predatory pricing (ii) SAA was poaching key staff (iii) SAA had concluded agreements with travel agents in terms of which they received commissions o
n an incremental basis that it alleged had an exclusionary effect (iv) SAA had a reward scheme for employees of travel agents, known as \'93Explorer\'94, which it was also alleged had an exclusionary effect. }
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj\tx720{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af7\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs24\lang2057\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057 
