 in the original Nationwide complaint, viz. those that relate to the incentive schemes for travel agents and the Explorer scheme. The other practices complained of have not found their way into the case before us nor has Nationwide pursued them by way of a
 non-referral.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0 At the time of the referral in casu the Commission stated that it was continuing to investigate the predatory pricing and the poaching complaints. See paragraph 5.2 of the complaint referral, Record, page 5.}}}
{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af14\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af14\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 } It would appear that the reason for the Commission\'92s selection of certain practices to constitute the basis of its present referral, are that similar practices have been scrutinised in cases in other countries and the Commission has sought 
to rely on this jurisprudence in this case.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af7\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs20\lang2057\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch   }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0 We refer to these cases later in this decision in the section dealing with the efficiency justification.}}}
