ary effects of the scheme on the complainant and \'93other competitors\'94.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0 See amendment to the Complaint referral Record page 185.}}}
{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af14\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af14\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177 } It is common cause that the only other competitor at the time was Comair Limited a company which operates a passenger service in the Southern African region. By virtue of a licence from
 British Airways, it uses the name BA/Comair. We will for this reason refer to this firm as BA/Comair.}
