\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s18\qj\tx720{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af7\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs24\lang2057\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f7\lang2057\i\f9\fs24\i\f7\lang1025\i\qj\tx540 15.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s18\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af7\afs24\lang1025\ai\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs24\lang2057\i\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057\i{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057\i\b0{ The SAA override incentive scheme works in this way. Agents receive a flat basic commission for all sales up to a target figure that is set for them in the contract. The target figure is expressed in rand value. If they exceed the target they become eligib
le for two further types of commission that are paid over and above the basic commission, which continues to be paid on sales over the target. The first category is what is termed the \'91override commission\'92. This is an additional commission paid if the agen
t meets and exceeds the target. However, the override commission is not limited to the amount above the target, but is payable on the total of all sales achieved above and below the target. Thus assume the firm has a target of sales set at R 100 million. I
f it exceeds this target by R 10 million it will receive an override commission, typically set at 0,5%, on all it sales i.e. it will amount to R 550 000. Note because the firm continues to receive its basic commission of 7% as well, the average rate would 
now be 7,5%. Because the override commission is payable on all sales earned, even those below the target, it is referred to as the \'91back to rand one\'92 principle. In some contracts the override commission is set at a constant rate, in others, it is subject t
o a continual increase as the firm\'92s sales reach continually higher targets. Thus in the American Express contract the override rate is a constant 0,5%.}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057\i\b0{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0{\cf1 See figures bundle 1 page 14 and Appendix 1 of this decision}}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0{\cf1\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i .}}}}
{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af14\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af14\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177\rtlch\ai\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i }{  In the Luxavia agreement, the override rate increases the more the agent exceeds its target.}{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up10\rtlch\af14\afs24\lang255\ltrch\dbch\af14\langfe255\hich\f1\fs24\lang7177\loch\f1\fs24\lang7177\rtlch\ai\ltrch\dbch\hich\i\loch\i  {\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\af7\afs20\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs20\lang2057\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0 See Appendix 1 of this decision.}}}
}{ The ra
te starts at 0,5% when the firm reaches its target, but moves to as high as 1,55%, if it exceeds its target by 25%. The figures show that if it attains its peak override commission at this level, it would not only earn a base commission of around R 37 mill
ion, it would also earn an override commission on top of that of R 8 million.}}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s18\qj\tx720{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af7\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs24\lang2057\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f7\lang2057\f9\fs24\f7\lang1025\qj\tx540 16.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s18\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af7\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs24\lang2057\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 But there is also a second category of commission for which the firm that exceeds its target is eligible and this is referred to as the \'91incremental commission\'92. If the travel agent earns a certain percentage of sales above target it then becomes eligible 
for this additional commission. This commission, unlike the override commission, is payable only on the amount above the target and is not therefore back to rand one, but is \'91back to rand base\'92. For this reason the incremental commission rate is typically 
much higher than the override and base commission rate, and in some agreements, is subject to escalation as well. Going back to our two models; in the American Express agreement, its incremental commission kicks in when it achieves sales in excess of 15% o
f its base target. The incremental rate commences at 14% for sales 15% above target, but rises steeply so that sales 35% above target are rewarded at a rate of 31%. Note the effect this has on the respective commissions. When American Express gets to 15% a
bove target its basic commission is about R6,3 million while its incremental commission (14%) amounts to R1.6 million. When it reaches its peak at 35% sales above target its basic commission is R7,4 million, but its incremental commission (31%) is now R 8,
5 million thus exceeding the basic commission.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s18\qj\tx720{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af7\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs24\lang2057\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057 
\par \pard\plain {\listtext\pard\plain \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\f7\lang2057\f9\fs24\f7\lang1025\qj\tx540 17.\tab}\ilvl0 \ltrpar\s18\qj\tx540{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ls1\li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\rtlch\af7\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs24\lang2057\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057 {\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057\i0\b0 The Luxavia agreement also has an incremental commission although it is structured differently. Here the incremental commission kicks in when sales are 5% above target, although the rate starts at only 5% and increases to a rate of 20% for sales that excee
d the target by 25%. It thus differs slightly from the American Express structure in that the incremental commission starts becoming payable earlier, but at a lower rate and reaches a lower peak commission.}
\par \pard\plain \ltrpar\s18\qj\tx720{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\rtlch\af7\afs24\lang1025\ltrch\dbch\af9\langfe255\hich\f7\fs24\lang2057\loch\f7\fs24\lang2057 
