ission failed to establish a causal link between the schemes and the expansion of SAA in the market, and the corresponding demise of its rivals, but that it has also failed to demonstrate harm to consumers.{\super \chftn{\*\footnote \chftn\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\ql\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch{\*\cs45\cf0{\*\updnprop5801}\up8\rtlch\ltrch\dbch\hich\loch}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch  }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch\f7\fs20\lang2057\i0\b0 SAA contests the evidence of this trend but also offers an alternative theory, assuming the trend is correct, for why it happened that is not causally linked to the incentive scheme in operation at the time.}}}
